HEADWORD: Ptenoglossa
<hw>Pte`no*glos"sa</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL.,
fr. Gr.<?/ feathered + <?/ tongue.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
division of gastropod mollusks having the teeth of the radula arranged
in long transverse rows, somewhat like the barbs of a feather.</def>⟦br⟧
